<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="41">Measurements and variation.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="41">
Variation of measurements (mm) and ratios for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Chevrolat" baseAuthorityYear="1863" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Semiardistomis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyaneolimbatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="41">Semiardistomis cyaneolimbatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(n=7) are: HL = 0,52- 0,59- 0,60; PL = 1,00- 1,03- 1,10; PW = 1,10- 1,18- 1,30; EL = 2,44- 2,72- 2,84; EW = 1,60- 1,75- 1,88; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="41">SBL =</emphasis>
3,96- 4,34- 4,54; PW/EW = 0,67; PW/PL = 1,14; PL/EL = 0,38; EW/EL = 0,64.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
