<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="42" type="habitat and activity">
<paragraph pageId="23" pageNumber="42">
<pageBreakToken pageId="23" pageNumber="42" start="start">Habitat</pageBreakToken>
and activity.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="23" pageNumber="42">
I collected this species along margins of the river Itabo, Isla de Pinos, Cuba (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 53" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 53. Habitat of Semiardistomis cyaneolimbatus (Chevrolat) at Rio Itabo, Isla de Pinos, Cuba." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/19674" pageId="23" pageNumber="42">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
); the adults were active during the day on wet, organic soil. Other specimens were collected about 8 meters from the river margins under leaf litter in shady gallery forest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
